apt search ddd

you must have compiled the source code with the -g flag to enable debugging

open the graphical user interface of the graphical debugger and select the executable file desired

The debugger will automatically find the .c file based on information that gcc leaves in the executable. This is useful when debugging a program that uses multiple source files.

Set breakpoints at the desired function(s) after the (gdb) prompt in the bottom window by typing `b func_name`

Execute the program by typing the following command at the (gdb) prompt: run

The program will start, and then pause at the breakpoint of function chosen

To continue the program, type the following command: continue

To view the call stack ask for the backtrace by inputting the following command: bt. The output
will be lines which will correspond to function frames of the call stack.

to select a frame enter `f frame_number`